-- ‘Too Many to Fail’ May Replace ‘Too Big to Fail,’ Sands Says
-- B y   L i a m   V a u g h a n
-- 2012-01-27T13:13:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/-too-many-to-fail-may-replace-too-big-to-fail-sands-says.html
Standard Chartered Plc (STAN)  Chief
Executive Officer  Peter Sands  said the threat of banks
being “too many to fail” may replace the risk of them being
“too big to fail.”  The world needs big banks, he said at a Bloomberg
Television debate at the  World Economic Forum  in Davos,
 Switzerland  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
